    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="999"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d999">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/3693</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        French Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JJAAJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jusserand</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1694</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to the Department’s note of
                    December 29 last,<note n="1" xml:id="d999fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_881">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, Supplement, p.
                        881</ref>.</note> regarding the presence of the French cruiser <hi
                        rend="italic">Descartes</hi> in the vicinity of San Juan, and various
                    incidents connected therewith, and your personal note of December 30 last,<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d999fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_882">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 882</ref>.</note> in which you stated
                    that you were making the necessary inquiries on the points mentioned in my <pb
                        facs="1051" n="765" xml:id="pg_765"/> note, I have the honor to ask whether
                    you have received any replies to your inquiries.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
